				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/kalinin" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2203795); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2203795&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610182905" alt="Kalinin" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2203795)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/kalinin" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2203795); return false;" >Kalinin</a></span> <span class="odate time_1439840303 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">17 Aug 2015 19:38</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2359451">
									

<p>Neutral vote. It's written to a degree of technical skill and thoughtfulness that it's an immersive document and a good exercise in the format, so it serves as a decent example of tone and execution. I will also note that it's not excessively long or sporting filler addenda, which is an increasing issue these days. Suffice to say, it's well-written enough and emblematic enough of the good qualities of a mainlist article that I can't downvote.</p>
<p>Conceptually, I'm left somewhat cold. Leaving aside the bells and whistles of the writeup, at heart it's a video game what transports the player into the game, which is kind of a predictable and well-worn trope in fiction since the 1980s. Does that disqualify something from being good? No, but I think there needs to be a little more narrative there for me to be invested in such a thing. The Wondertainment reference isn't as obnoxious as those usually are since it didn't come with all of the attendant Willy Wonka palette-swap goofiness that those usually entail, but there also really wasn't any reason for it be there either, aside from a default association between that concept and products intended for children.</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Also,&nbsp;a&nbsp;personal&nbsp;nitpick</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Though&nbsp;it's&nbsp;generally&nbsp;applicable</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<blockquote>
<p>The creation of non-euclidean space</p>
</blockquote>
<p>This is something on the level of &quot;amnesiac&quot; for me in terms of misuse of a scientific concept. &quot;Non-euclidean&quot; refers to a space that, to simplify matters greatly, does not consist of a two-dimensional plane. Which, of course, is reality. We <em>live</em> in non-Euclidean space. I'm not trying to single you out personally, as this has become kind of a default usage on the wiki, but I don't care for &quot;non-Euclidean&quot; as a synonym for &quot;spatial anomaly,&quot; because that's not what it means.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<p>The technical skill on display is considerable, and I respect it. But the content isn't quite there for me.</p>

							</div>

								
					
